      "role": "user",
      "content": "idk i dont think its just drafts or something. it feels way too specific. like i was literally just sitting there alone and the temperature dropped the second i started getting upset. and the fridge makes this specific low hum too. isnt it possible there's some kind of background data protocol or mesh network thing where they talk to each other about local environment changes? like a way they could be monitoring patterns without me seeing it in an app?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
