      "content": "Smart home protocols like Zigbee or Matter cannot directly access or measure human emotional states, so they have no reason to create such a specific, simultaneous chain of events. The only way for devices to coordinate instantly is through local control circuitry within a single unit, which explains why there is no traceable data trail in your app logs. While the timing feels too perfect to be random, without evidence of intentional device-to-device logic designed to monitor human physiology, the most probable explanation remains a rare electronic glitch or an unrelated environmental factor coinciding with your reaction.",
